LAGOS – Dr Junaid Mohammed, elder statesman and the Second Republic federal lawmaker on Tuesday said Dr. Ango Ab­dullahi, the Chairman of the Northern Elders Forum (NEF), was not speaking for the entire North when he said the north is ready for the restructuring of Nigeria to make it more viable. Speaking in an interview with Daily Independent, Ju­naid said Ango Abdullahi is at liberty to speak for himself or the Northern Elders Forum but his stance on restructuring should not be mistaken as the general position of the North. He said, “I don’t know how with due modesty one individ­ual can claim to speak for the entire North. It is impossible. You are talking about 100 mil­lion people. That, however, does not deny him the right to speak for himself or for the Northern Elders Forum for whom he speaks if he wishes to do so.” EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “We have to be very care­ful about making claims on behalf of the North, South, East or West. If you have been following my statements, I have never claimed to speak for the North or speak for anybody. Whenever I spoke, I speak for myself as an individual and I have the right to do that in a democracy”. “Besides, I have a lot of prob­lems with this issue because unless restructuring has been defined, I am not prepared to waste my time talking about an issue that for every 10 Nige­rians, there are about 15 defi­nitions. Unless restructuring has been defined and there is a universal agreement on what restructuring is, I am not pre­pared to argue on a concept that there is no agreement. This is because we will not be saying the same thing”. Crossover Night: CAN Asks Churches To Close Services By 11p.m Customers Resort To PoS Amid Disappointing Bank ATMs “Don’t you ever take what­ever any northerner says when he says he is speaking for the north? Even during the days of A